.TH _PRINTF 3 "2025-11-26" "v1.0" "_printf Manual"

.SH NAME
_printf \- Format and print data

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B _printf
_printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B _printf
displays text formatted according to a string passed as an argument. 
It supports certain specifiers such as %c, %s, %d, %i, etc.
The function works similarly to the standard printf function in C.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed.  
If an output error occurs (for example, if the underlying write fails), it returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
/* Print value */
_printf("Value : %d\n", 42);
OUTPUT:
Value : 42

/* Print signed value */
_printf("Signed value : %i\n", -98);
OUTPUT:
Signed value : -98

/* Print string */
_printf("Name : %s\n", "Bonjour");
OUTPUT:
Name : Bonjour

/* Print multiple formats */
_printf("Char: %c, String: %s, Number: %d\n", 'A', "Test", 123);
OUTPUT:
Char: A, String: Test, Number: 123

/* Print percentage */
_printf("Progress: 100%% complete\n");
OUTPUT:
Progress: 100% complete
.fi

